import React from "react";

const IconComponent = ({ className }) => (
  <svg
    width="40"
    height="40"
    viewBox="0 0 40 40"
    fill="none"
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
    xmlnsXlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    className={className} // Apply the passed className
  >
    <rect width="40" height="40" rx="8" fill="#28124D" />
    <mask
      id="mask0_2_383"
      style={{ maskType: "alpha" }}
      maskUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
      x="8"
      y="8"
      width="24"
      height="24"
    >
      <rect
        x="8.66675"
        y="8.66663"
        width="22.6667"
        height="22.6667"
        fill="url(#pattern0_2_383)"
      />
    </mask>
    <g mask="url(#mask0_2_383)">
      <rect width="40" height="40" rx="20" fill="white" />
    </g>
    <defs>
      <pattern
        id="pattern0_2_383"
        patternContentUnits="objectBoundingBox"
        width="1"
        height="1"
      >
        <use xlinkHref="#image0_2_383" transform="scale(0.0104167)" />
      </pattern>
      <image
        id="image0_2_383"
        width="96"
        height="96"
        xlinkHref="data:image/png;base64,"
      />
    </defs>
  </svg>
);

export default IconComponent;
